title: Part A
stimulusHtml:
2 Points

1 - Price increases as a result of the demand increase

1 - Quantity remains the same
descriptions:
The student earns none of the following points:

1 - Price increases as a result of the demand increase

1 - Quantity remains the same

The student earns one of the following points:

1 - Price increases as a result of the demand increase

1 - Quantity remains the same

The student earns all of the following points:

1 - Price increases as a result of the demand increase

1 - Quantity remains the same

title: Part B
stimulusHtml:
2 Points

  • 1 - Setting the price ceiling below the equilibrium price.

  • 1 - Quantity demanded increases

  • 1/2 - Quantity supplied unchanged
descriptions:
The student earns none of the following points:

  • 1 - Setting the price ceiling below the equilibrium price.

  • 1 - Quantity demanded increases

  • 1/2 - Quantity supplied unchanged

The student earns one of the following points:

  • 1 - Setting the price ceiling below the equilibrium price.

  • 1 - Quantity demanded increases

  • 1/2 - Quantity supplied unchanged

The student earns all of the following points:

  • 1 - Setting the price ceiling below the equilibrium price.

  • 1 - Quantity demanded increases

  • 1/2 - Quantity supplied unchanged

title: Part C
stimulusHtml:
1 Point

1 - for no, a secondary market or reselling of tickets or scalping of tickets will have some circus-goers paying more than the ceiling price.
descriptions:
The student earns none of the following points:

1 - for no, a secondary market or reselling of tickets or scalping of tickets will have some circus-goers paying more than the ceiling price.

The student earns all of the following points:

  • 1 - for no, a secondary market or reselling of tickets or scalping of tickets will have some circus-goers paying more than the ceiling price.
